 The City Diary
																																																																																		Gita Mandal, 16, an inmate of Liluah Home for Destitute Women, fled from Howrah District Hospital on Monday around 11.30pm. She was taken to the hospital after she complained of chest pain. The home authorities have lodged a missing diary with Bally police. Santhia police arrested Gita after she was found loitering in 2004. Niraj Kumar Singh, the superintendent of police (Howrah), said the girl had attempted to flee the home in 2004.																																																		Motorcyclist Bappa Haldar, 18, was killed and his pillion-rider Goutam Das was seriously injured when the two-wheeler dashed against a lamp post early on Wednesday on NSC Bose Road, in Jadavpur.																																																		Swapna Roy, 29, a homemaker in Lake Town, hanged herself on Wednesday morning. Police said Swapna was suffering from depression. 
